fix bug in icap test
scripts. update packer template to
generate ova when create_ova variable
is true.

- Simplified instructions that can
help setup the framework in
10 mins - Error Rate
% in Performance Dashboard -
Better error case troubleshooting option
to analyze files before and
after processing. - Test Data
bucket will contain out folder
and it will have files
in case of error situations.
- Each prefix will have
own folder with those files.
- Setup link to configure
the framework - Single click
Update button to update to
latest version of the framework.

- Instructions simplified - Bugs
fixed - New setup UI
introduced

* UI Updates - interface
supports trigger load - UI
Interface supports load agains direct
icap, via proxy offline site
and proxied Sharepoint - stop
tests from UI - performance
test summary results table *
ICAPServer Performance Test and Analytics
Ubuntu AMI is published in
all supported regions (AWS Ireland,
North Virginia, Oregon and North
California) * Implemented results automatic
analyser. * Both dashboard and
load generators are now based
on Ubuntu 20.04 * Weekly
packer build AMI/OVA with github
actions.

- Configured AWS Cloud Formation
stack to automatically create the
infrastructure to generate traffic &
run tests - Implemented input
mechanism to retrieve required files
for processing from S3 -
Implemented assertion mechanism that
validates
the response code returned from
ICAP server. - Implemented Influx
DB logging solution to log
the performance metrics - Implemented
monitoring feature using Grafana for
detailed metrics dashboard display -
Implemented the mechanism to dynamically
create EC2 instances based on
the number of users in
the test run. - Implemented
a mechanism to dynamically assign
users to each ec2 instance.

First tag with stable version
of gp-load-balancer

- JMeter test plan is
configured to use ICAP client
to send traffic directly to
the ICAP server - Configured
kubernetes cluster with a traffic
generator and Docker image to
generate the number of pods
using the JMeter script. -
Implemented mechanism to retrieve required
files for processing from MinIO
- Implemented mechanism to output
processed files to MinIO -
Implemented assertion mechanism that
validates
the response code returned -
Implemented Influx DB UI Logging
to retrieve the performance logs
- Created Grafana dashboard to
visualize the test metrics to
show detailed metrics - Implemented
the ability to fetch the
ICAP server metrics to influx
DB

This release includes the following:
- Docker image that support
JMeter on OpenJDK 8 JRE
and icap-client - Github Action
for the deployment of Minio,
InfluxDB, ELK, Prometheus and Grafana
on native k8s clusters. -
Support for running Jobs using
Powershell script - Support JMX
script that: - use icap-client
for testing - copy test
results to Minio - send
test metrics to Grafana

Release Notes for v1.0.0 Policy
Management applied to files rebuilt
through Cloud Version. Maintained History
for Policy Management changes (Past/Current).
Added Glasswall icon in the
MAC build. Removed Electron from
Menu bar on MAC build.
Added Geotiff file support to
the Policy Management both Docker
and Cloud Analysis of files
rebuild has been integrated in
cloud and docker. New docker
rebuild image TAG integrated. Bugs
Fixes: Correct File is getting
saved on custom location after
rebuild. Fixed sorting in-case of
multi page Fixed alignment under
session page.

Release Notes for v0.9.0 Added
Threat Intelligence to the cloud
rebuild, Displayed threat level on
the UI Watermark added for
rebuild PDF file. Buy Token
feature added under setting. Bugs
Fixes: On rebuilding the file
using Cloud user is displayed
the wrong time under session.
Fixed sorting in-case of multi
page Fixed alignment under session
page. Fixed analysis report earlier
it was showing High for
all the files. Error message
being displayed incase file is
blocked due to Policy. Fixed
alignment on mouse hover on
Flat and Hierarchy label on
Cloud and Docker page Session
page not getting loaded in
case no session is present.
Raw Logs added in multi-line
format in case logs are
very long. (Removed horizontal scroll
bar) Color of all the
buttons under different pages made
in sync. Aligned the text
on each page Provide an
interface to update the GW
image name. Saving files in
destination folder as it get
processed.

Release Notes for v0.1.7 Policy
Control & Management : UI
and Backend (Policy view, Edit,
Save, Apply to docker container).
Threat Analysis : Integrated Threat
analysis of files rebuilt with
docker. Integrated processing target with
rebuilt sessions metadata : Cloud/Docker.
UI Enhancement and some minor
fixes.

Release Notes for v0.1.6 Added
support for Parallel & Sequential
execution of requests with docker.
Added Threat Intelligence to the
application, Displayed threat level on
the UI. Session History: Added
session history tab which list
all the rebuild sessions (Cloud
and Local). Rebuild & File
analysis event logging: Added separate
tab to capture RAW logs
using a file backed logger.
Made server configuration configurable. Fixed
google universal analytics issues and
downloads are now visible on
GA. UI Enhancement and some
minor fixes.

Release Notes for v0.1.5 Local
rebuild health check : To
check the local rebuild configuration
and it state    
    a) If docker
Installed.        
b)f docker running.    
    c) If GW
image present else pull.  
      d) If
GW image licensed. Health check
event logging: Added the event
logs for docker health check.
Rebuild & File analysis event
logging: Added the event logs
for local Rebuild and file
analysis. Added health check functionality
on UI. Made output path
persistent across rebuilds. UI Enhancement
and some minor fixes

Release Notes for v0.1.4 Processing
rebuild locally through Docker after
pulling the docker image. Creating
analysis report for rebuilt files
locally through Docker. Added option
for User to rebuild app
either locally or through cloud.
Modified the ReadMe with steps
to run rebuild locally through
docker. Added option for User
to rebuild app either locally
or through cloud. Git link
for above changes:
https://github.com/k8-proxy/glasswall-
desktop/pull/95 Creating
analysis report for rebuilt files
locally through Docker.

## Features/Changes - Updates to
dashboard: new charts and fixes
for edge cases. - Added
test Ids for puppeteer tests.

Styling updates for Jake. Improved
Date Time picker.

## Features/Changes Updated components and
bug fixes. Styling updates.

## Features/Changes - Styling Updates
- CSS Transitions - Improved
File Drop - Improved Date
pickers

## Features/Changes Enhanced navbar.
Kubernetes
service and deployment defined. Helm
chart created. CI workflow for
kubernetes + helm validation and
testing. Installed react-dropzone, react-
promise-tracker, react-toast-notifications
and react-xml-parser. ### File Drop
Page File drop page now
works locally, can drop a
file and it will be
sent to the same file
drop API as [file-drop.co.uk](https://file-
drop.co.uk/). The
File Drop React code has
been ported from the file-drop
site as well.

- Dashboard - Updates to
request history page - Udates
to policy page - Styling
updates - Change to CI/CD
workflows (new build script for
gh-pages) - Chart.js and react-chartjs-2
installed

## Features/Changes More styling and
css updates. SOW Checklist view
added, link from the login
page under the 'Forgotten Password'
link. ### Request History Page
File Type and Outcome filters
added. Date-Time Picker added. File
Info modal updated to cover
more of the screen, rather
than a sidebar. Can now
sort by each column in
the table (timestamp, alphabetical file
type etc...). ### Policy Page
Moved links from navbar to
tabs on the policy page.
'Current' tab now has Allow/Sanitise
radio toggles added for each
file type. 'History' tab now
has a table with an
example previous policy. Modal not
implemented

css updates - MaterialUI Installed
- Backdrop component ### Request
History Page - Requests Table

- Filter component - Checkbox
component

and skip if it contains

* Processed 18k gov uk
site files via test data
solution and syncing to s2
* Change hashing method from
sha-1 to share-256 * Process
and generate metadata in postgres
db for virus files *
Document how test data solution
can be used for normal
files * Test files with
different type of supported compression
Zip, 7z, gz, tar, rar_
* Create a program to
create a multilevel compressed test
file with malicious content. *
Configured Postgres db to capture
metadata * Compressed file generator
* Multilevel compression * Batch
processing added for both scraper
and file processor * Space
and ec2 bug fixes

### Features * Integration of
Distribution Api , GW_crawler ,
Storage , Rabbit mq ,
glass_rebuild , file processor and
s3 sync modules * File
processing bug fixes, support for
icap_rebuild file and xml report,
fixed processing of zip files
* Exception handling in all
places * Sy sync and
creating folder in s3 and
storing files under extension name
as folder name * The
integration is tested and imporved
efficiency * Deployment of codebase
in ec2 instance * Bundle
zip will contain metadata.json, rebuild_xml
, rebuild file , virustotal
report, original file inside zip
file * Gloabl hashing is
done and the files in
bundle zip are stored with
hash name * Collection of
10000 files in glasswall s3
under bucket k8-test-data ( in
progress ) * Refactoring of
api calls configartable from .env
files

Fixes on v0.1.1: 1.- Some
zip files were not processed
and moved directly to error
folder. The reason was that
the zip files were almost
200mb. 2.- Logs are improved:
Log folder contains logs from
files that are not processed
correctly. Other log details can
be found in GlasswallFileProcessingStatus.txt
under
each processed zip file (in
both error or output folder).
